One of the worst experiences I’ve ever had at a restaurant! We arrived for our dinner reservation with no one attending to the hostess station and had to track down the owner to ask about being seated. The front of the restaurant was packed with people who had been waiting for tables (some for over an hour and a half). We were promised our table for ten would be ready in 10 minutes and an hour and 15 minutes later, after repeatedly reminding the owner that we were waiting to be seated for our 5:30 reservation, they seated 3 other large parties ahead of us who had 6:00 reservations. We never got to eat because we had tickets to a 7:00 show. I even called the day of the reservation, multiple times, to confirm that they would have our table ready for us with a reservation. They didn’t care that they had completely disrespected us and were very dismissive when we told them we were unhappy about how we were treated and couldn’t wait any longer. We never got to try the food, but I have a hard time believing it would have been worth the wait. The sad part is that we were warned by multiple people that this would happen and we still gave them the benefit of the doubt that a reservation meant something. You’ll be disappointed before you even get to a table if you try to eat here!!!
